An unincorporated nonprofit association may be dissolved as follows:
If the governing principles provide a time or method for dissolution, at that time or by that method;
If the governing principles do not provide a time or method for dissolution, upon approval by the members;
If no member can be located and the associationâ€™s operations have been discontinued for at least three (3) years, by the managers or, if the association has no current manager, by its last manager;
By court order; or
Under law other than this chapter.
